Sec. 161.003. DUTY OF COUNTY COMMISSIONERS COURT. (a) The
commissioners court of each county shall cooperate with and assist
the commission in protecting livestock, domestic animals, and
domestic fowl from communicable diseases, regardless of whether a
particular disease exists in the county.
(b) Each commissioners court may employ a veterinarian at the
expense of the county. Any veterinarian employed is subject to
approval by the commission.
Acts 1981, 67th Leg., p. 1393, ch. 388, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 1981.

